          },
          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The neutrons emitted in the bombardment of B-10 and",
                "B-11 by deuterons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,PPS/A,62,586,1949",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,PPS/A,62,586,1949",
                    "doi": "10.1088/0370-1298/62/9/306",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "PPS/A",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "62",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "586"
                      },
                      "date": 1949
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "W.M.Gibson"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2UK CAV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2UK CAV"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLATE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ilford C.2 plates, with emulsion thicknesses",
                "varying from 250 mum to 290 mum, were held in light-",
                "tight boxes so that they received at grazing incidence",
                "the neutrons emitted from the target at right angles to",
                "the direction of the deuteron beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The specimens of the separated isotopes were in the",
                "form of thin deposits on the copper sheet. The",
                "thicknesses were such that the energy loss of a",
                "deuteron passing through the B-ll layer was of the",
                "order of 120 keV and through the B-l0 layer 30 keV, the",
                "separation of the isotopes was practically complete."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "To obtain the actual distribution of neutron number",
                "with energy, it was necessary to correct these spectra",
                "for two effects-the variation of neutron-proton",
                "scattering cross section with energy and the variation",
                "with energy of the fraction of the proton tracks which",
                "would be expected to remain within the emulsion.",
                "The correction factor is normalized to unity at 7 MeV,",
                "so that in the corrected spectra of Figures 2,3 and 4",
                "the ordinates around this energy represent actual",
                "numbers of tracks measured, while being proportional to",
                "neutron numbers at all energies. The effect of the",
                "variation of the correction factor is shown by the",
                "standard deviations indicated on the corrected spectra."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The uncertainty is reported by authors on",
                "figure."
              ]
            }
          ],
